A vintage-style illustration depicting two identical antique pocket watches floating in space, their inner gears and mechanisms exposed and intertwining where they meet in the middle. Bronze and copper cogs from each watch attempt to mesh together but clash at certain points, with some gears spinning in opposite directions. Small sparks of golden light emerge from the friction points. The background is a deep sepia-toned void with faint circular ripples emanating outward from the collision point, suggesting synchronized time waves disrupting each other. The watches trail delicate chains that spiral and weave around each other like DNA helixes. Warm amber and burnished metal tones dominate, with aged patina textures on all surfaces giving an authentic early 20th century technical illustration feel.
